abstract: Bernie Sanders won New Hampshire’s presidential primary, edging moderate rival Pete Buttigieg and scoring the first clear victory in the Democratic Party’s chaotic 2020 nomination fight.
snippet: Bernie Sanders won New Hampshire’s presidential primary, edging moderate rival Pete Buttigieg and scoring the first clear victory in the Democratic Party’s chaotic 2020 nomination fight.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Bernie Sanders won New Hampshire’s presidential primary, edging moderate rival Pete Buttigieg and scoring the first clear victory in the Democratic Party’s chaotic 2020 nomination fight.
headline_main: Sanders Edges Buttigieg in NH, Giving Dems 2 Front-Runners
headline_print_headline: Sanders Edges Buttigieg in NH, Giving Dems 2 Front-Runners

abstract: Trustbusting advocates like Sarah Miller, who target corporate power, have finally found themselves at the center of the political conversation.
snippet: Trustbusting advocates like Sarah Miller, who target corporate power, have finally found themselves at the center of the political conversation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One night five years ago, Sarah Miller, a former Treasury Department aide, was trying to make sense of an economic recovery that had left the country in the grips of rising inequality.

headline_main: What’s at Stake in the New Hampshire Primary
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa.
snippet: Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa...
lead_paragraph: HAMPTON, N.H. — Joe Biden had spent much of the weekend ahead of New Hampshire's primary on Tuesday attacking his top Democratic presidential rivals when a young woman asked why voters should believe he could win a national election after his poor showing in Iowa.
headline_main: Biden Shows Tenderness and Temper on 2020 Presidential Trail
headline_print_headline: Biden Shows Tenderness and Temper on 2020 Presidential Trail

abstract: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
snippet: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Two days before a once-mission-critical primary in a state she neighbors, Senator Elizabeth Warren — typically exceptional at holding a room — had not finished speaking when something unusual happened: Dozens of voters began filtering out of the middle school gym she had reserved.

abstract: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
snippet: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
lead_paragraph: DERRY, N.H. — Throughout the nearly half century-long presidential rivalry between Iowa and New Hampshire, sometimes a state has to dig deep to make its case for why its contest is in fact superior.

abstract: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg's shadow over the Democratic presidential race grew a bit longer on Tuesday after his surprise write-in win in a hamlet that traditionally kicks off voting in New Hampshire's closely watched primary election.
snippet: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg's shadow over the Democratic presidential race grew a bit longer on Tuesday after his surprise write-in win in a hamlet that traditionally kicks off voting in New Hampshire's closely watched primary ele...
lead_paragraph: DIXVILLE NOTCH, N.H. — Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg's shadow over the Democratic presidential race grew a bit longer on Tuesday after his surprise write-in win in a hamlet that traditionally kicks off voting in New Hampshire's closely watched primary election.
headline_main: Bloomberg Turns Heads With Write-In Win in New Hampshire Hamlet
